def: A manganese phosphate near triplite, but containing hydroxylinstead of fluorine.
To discipline; to correct. [Obs.]And bitter Penance, with an iron whip, Was wont him once to displeevery day. Spenser.
Fountain; source.The headspring of our belief. Stapleton.
A mode or process of painting; distemper.
The second element in each half of a hemal arch, correspondingto the sternal part of a rib. Owen.-- Hem`a*po*phys"i*al, a.

Having the nature, properties, or qualities, of an adult man;characteristic of developed manhood; hence, masterful; forceful;specifically, capable of begetting; -- opposed to womanly, feminine,and puerile; as, virile age, virile power, virile organs.
A division of Mollusca having slender, cirriform appendagesnear the mouth; the Scaphopoda.
The act of interceding; intercession; intervention. [R.] Bp.Reynolds.
